-- Dubai's Amlak shareholders to meet Sept 21 on restructuring plan
-- By David French
-- Wed Sep 03, 2014 06:41AM EDT
-- None



DUBAI, Sept 3 (Reuters) - Dubai mortgage lender Amlak Finance <AMLK.DU> said on Wednesday that it would hold a shareholder meeting on Sept. 21 to discuss its restructuring plan and a proposed issue of equity-linked bonds.

Creditors of the company, whose shares have been suspended since late 2008 after it was hit by a local real estate crash and the global financial crisis, last month approved a plan to restructure debts worth around $2.7 billion. [ID:nL6N0QD46V] Shareholders will meet later this month to discuss the restructuring plan and the company's financial outlook, a statement to the Dubai bourse said on Wednesday.